               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#ai-catalogue">
                     <p>ایقان</p>
                     <p>For this MS. of the Iqan see pp. 435-438 of my Catalogue and Description of
                        <lb/>27 Bábí Manuscripts. A French translation of this important work by M.
                        Hippolyte <lb/>Dreyfus was published in Paris in 1904 under the title of Le
                        Livre de la Certitude. <lb/>See my Materials for the Study of the Bábí
                        Religion, pp. 12 and n. 1 ad calc., 179, <lb/>and 325.</p>
                     <p>Browne does not name the author explicitly within his 1892 entry, but the
                        attribution to Bahá'u'lláh is implicit throughout his discussion of the
                        work's date of composition and is standard in the secondary literature.</p>
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="F_58-item1">
                     <author key="person_88702713" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/88702713/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Baháʼuʼlláh,
                           1817-1892</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">بهاء الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_898">Īqān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_898">ايقان</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_898">Book of Certitude</title>

                     <note>Composed two years after Bahá'u'lláh's return to Baghdad from the
                        mountains of Kurdistan, i.e. in A.H. 1274 (A.D. 1858-9), "while he still
                        owned allegiance to Ṣubḥ-i-Ezel." See also: <ref
                           target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_630">F.
                        59 (BBA. 2)</ref></note> 
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar" defective="true"/>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <ref target="https://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/PR-A-00233-00004/105"
                              >p.79</ref>
                        </bibl>
                        <bibl>See sub classmark <idno>BBP. 1</idno> in Browne's "Catalogue and
                           Description of 27 Bābī Manuscripts", in Journal of the Royal Asiatic
                           Society of Great Britain and Ireland (Jul., 1892): 433-499.</bibl>
                        <bibl type="text-relations"/>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian, with Arabic
                        quotations</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="paper">
                        <support>Paper</support>
                        <extent>82 folios (ff. 1a, 81b, 82a, and 82b blank) <dimensions type="leaf"
                              unit="cm">
                              <height>22.25</height>
                              <width>11.25</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <condition>Twice damaged, per Browne: first by the bursting open of a
                           portable ink-bottle with which it was packed, staining the margins of the
                           leaves; second by the adhesion of a number of opposite leaves to one
                           another (either from undue pressure or unusual stickiness of the ink),
                           leaving parts of the text "almost illegible" at the time Browne wrote
                           (1892), although he notes it "was in good condition" when he first
                           described it in 1888.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout writtenLines="22">22 lines to the page.</layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote>Browne gives no description of the hand/script for this
                        item.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
